A_641 - In today's society, objects, even those with a short lifespan, are often accumulated and left unused for years. All those items of clothing or various toys that accompany us from the beginning of our lives until adulthood are often objects that, once used, could easily change owners, following a focus on reuse and reducing consumption. This would allow families to save on expenses, and since we're talking about a period of about twenty years, it certainly can't be said that's a negligible period.